<p><strong>Guidance:</strong></p>
<p lang="fr-FR">
  . Member States (MS) should provide a list of the main funding sources that
  will be mobilized to support the implementation of the proposed measures. The
  purpose is to assess if the proposed (new) measures can be made operational or
  not.
</p>
<p lang="fr-FR">
  The assessors should check if, for each measure/measure fiche:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      The funding sources (national and/or European) are presented.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p lang="fr-BE">
      The Community financial instruments, in accordance with applicable rules
      and conditions; is presented.
    </p>
  </li>
</ul>
<p>
  Based on the existing information, the assessors should select:
  &ldquo;Yes&rdquo; if the financing sources are presented for all (new)
  measures, &ldquo;Partially&rdquo; if the financing sources are presented for
  some of the (new) measures, &ldquo;No&rdquo; if the information on the funding
  sources is not presented, and &ldquo;No Information&rdquo; if no information
  on the financing sources is mentioned.
</p>
